  journal: "medRxiv / Int J Med Rev Case Rep (target)"
  doi:   # placeholder — replace on acceptance

# Honest disclosure required by the licence (Apache 2.0 §4(c)).
abstract: >-
  Nutramilo Insulin Score (NIS) is a deterministic, source-aware computational
  surrogate for the Holt Food Insulin Index. Four frozen OLS coefficients
  (per-1000-kJ density of carbohydrate, protein, fat, fiber) trained on a
  public n=147 Holt-Bell-Bao cohort, augmented with plant/mixed/animal source
  multipliers, an energy-normalised pure-fat extrapolation guard, an optional
  Le-2008 fructose split, and a cross-cohort linear calibration. Primary
  inferential evaluation is restricted to a strictly out-of-sample n=25
  literature-pooled subset. NIS v1.1.5 is positioned as an EXPLORATORY
  methodology study, not as an externally validated predictive model; a
  prospective CGM trial (Part II of the manuscript pair) is the planned
  confirmatory step.
